---
title: Sourdough Bread
source: Tartine Bakery
servings: 2 loaves
tags:
  - bread
  - sourdough
  - fermentation
---

= Levain

Mix @bread flour{200%g}, @whole wheat flour{50%g}, @water{200%g}(warm, 78°F),
and @sourdough starter{50%g}(active, bubbly) in a #medium bowl{}.

Cover and let ferment at room temperature for ~levain rise{12%hours}.

= Autolyse

Combine @bread flour{900%g}, @whole wheat flour{100%g}, and @water{700%g}(warm)
in a #large mixing bowl{}. Mix until no dry flour remains.

Rest for ~autolyse{1%hour}.

= Mix & Bulk Fermentation

Add the levain and @salt{20%g} to the dough. Squeeze and fold to incorporate.

Perform stretch-and-folds every ~{30%minutes} for the first 2 hours.

-- Total bulk fermentation is about 4 hours at 78°F.

Let rest undisturbed for ~bulk ferment{2%hours}.

= Shape & Proof

Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Divide into 2 pieces.

Pre-shape into rounds. Rest for ~bench rest{20%minutes}.

Final shape and place seam-side up in floured #bannetons{2}. Cover and
cold-proof in the refrigerator for ~cold proof{12-16%hours}.

= Bake

Preheat #oven and #dutch oven{} to 500°F for ~preheat{1%hour}.

Score the dough with a #lame{} or razor blade.

Bake covered for ~{20%minutes} at 500°F. Remove lid, reduce to 450°F,
and bake for another ~{20-25%minutes} until deep golden brown.
